NOTE:-you can use MAX(timestamp) from the target table instead of a watermark table But creating watermarktable is recommded when dataset is huge

THEORY:-"I use a watermark table to track the last processed timestamp. During each run, I fetch that value, filter the source data to get only the incremental records, and use a MERGE operation on a Delta table to handle both inserts and updates. After successful load, I update the watermark with the latest timestamp."

Watermark pattern is an incremental loading technique used to process only new or changed data based on a tracking column (usually a timestamp).



